// Url Normalization and join WebPlatform SD
// This module reads an input list of urls and provides followings output: 1. Normalized url: We transform url using the normalization rules. The idea here is strip the parameters that are deemed non-useful by the normalization team so as to be more efficient with our index space. Note all the urls in IndexGeneration system onwards have been normalized with these rules. For detailed info see (https://www.bingwiki.com/URL_Normalization) 2. RetroIndexKeyUrl: this is retroindexkey version of normalized url for joining with retroindex.3. HutHash: this is hash of normalized url that is  the identifier of document in many IS stacks. 
REFERENCE "/shares/searchWebLoad/RetroIndex/bin/ManagedUrlNormalizer.dll";
RESOURCE "/shares/searchWebLoad/RetroIndex/bin/NativeUrlNormalizer.dll";
REFERENCE "/shares/searchWebLoad/RetroIndex/bin/DpimScopeCommon.dll";
RESOURCE "/shares/searchWebLoad/RetroIndex/bin/DpimFormatting.dll";
RESOURCE "/shares/searchWebLoad/RetroIndex/bin/UrlNormalizerConfig.DP.ini";          
